or is that a style issue? <p>"And we didn't use the metal giant dragon thing <i>why?</i>"
<br> ~ Serra
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uziropump.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ZiroPump</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://santooma.tripod.com/button.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/27/01 2:03:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://santooma.tripod.com/button.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Inking then CG</span><hr size=1> You can really do it either way is just a personal issue really but if u shade it with the pen first it will have a more flat and comic book look than a 3d look. <p>"The world has ended and only i survie and then it sets in ......DAMN i didn't finish my art class!"

<img src=http://santooma.tripod.com/button.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uvine2000.showPublicProfile?language=EN>vine2000</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/27/01 2:07:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Inking in CG</span><hr size=1> I think it would be more of a style issue, and the look you are going for.<br>
<br>
Say you want a Golden or Silver Age comic book, or 1980's Manga look.  In this case I would probably do hatching and cross hatching in ink prior to coloring.<br>
<br>
If you want a newer look, I would focus on clean line art and do the shading in CG.  This is more the route for what you'll find in the tutorials here at Polykarbon with blend modes, etc.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps some. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uspikescafe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SpikesCafe</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.spikescafe.com/shell.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gamera</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/27/01 4:02:57 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.spikescafe.com/tortmoni.gif height=93 width=127></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Inking in CG</span><hr size=1> Well, Joe Mad and his Liquid colouring crew seem to do a little of both.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.joemadureira.com/">www.joemadureira.com/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
